            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>Did it Pay</head>
                <origin>Somerset Herald and Whig</origin>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Nill</ln>
                        <fn>James</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Asserts that, though successful in the election, the Union Movement is
                    splitting the Republican party.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Change of Tune</head>
                <origin>Philadelphia Bulletin</origin>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>The Bulletin reports that the previous election saw some Democratic gains
                    in the Pennsylvania legislature. It states that all the elected Democrats are
                    good Union men who favor vigorous prosecution of the war. The Spirit wants to
                    know why the Bulletin has changed its opinion--before the election, it labeled
                    Democrats secessionists.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
